by kevinvergauwen at 2014-05-23T09:28:00Z

@stof I was wondering why the application instance can't be injected in the Command constructor as an optional argument. In that case, the configure method, which is called by the constructor, can access the container. This is useful if input arguments depend on parameters of a bundle. There are no BC breaks as far as I can see by doing this.

